{
  "stem": "4753.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Where we arrived, also, to a big building, empty building.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There, after a few hours, or a day, later, people arrived with a Red Cross armband on the arm.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Later, I learned that was Swedish Red Cross, coming from Sweden.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Rescue unit took 2,000 inmates out from different camps, not only just us, because we were, in that time, very, very few.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We did go to Braunschweig, 850, and, no-- maybe we were, maybe we were, 40 or 50 alive.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And other camps came to that place, and 2,000 people were taken to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was 1st of May, and we were taken, with two SS men, to-- from Hamburg to Denmark, and we stopped by [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's the name of the city, you said I should show you the soap.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I will go.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [GERMAN], when we had to-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody left the train, or what happened, because my-- one of my girlfriends said she's dying, and I should bring her milk, because as we looked out on the window, the Danish people, God bless them, came with breads, and milks, and cheese, and I don't know what else.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Chocolate.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she wanted to have milk, so I got off from the train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one lady gave me a bottle of milk.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But in the next moment, another inmate grabbed out of my hand.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I started to cry, and the lady told me that, don't cry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I will bring you another bottle of milk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Just wait for me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She had a lot of bread, also.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
